Conway's Game of Life implementation complete. All 8 tests pass through the full TDD red-green-refactor cycle:

1. Empty input → []
2. Single isolated cell dies (underpopulation)
3. Two adjacent cells die (underpopulation)
4. 2x2 block remains unchanged (still life)
5. Vertical blinker oscillates to horizontal (survival + reproduction)
6. Fully-surrounded center cell dies (overpopulation)
7. Dead cell with 3 live neighbors is born (reproduction)
8. Negative coordinates handled correctly

The `experiment-done.txt` marker has been written.
